programme.title: Love Triangle Nightmare
programme.desc: Brittany meets a stranger who has everything she wants in a partner and despite being an unknown man as warned by others, she falls in love with him which leads to something tragic.

programme.title: The Night Stalker
programme.desc: Known to many as the "Night Stalker", Richard Ramirez was a cruel and prolific serial killer who murdered 14 people and terrorized Los Angeles in the summer of 1985. This film tells the story of Kit (Bellamy Young), an attorney who travels to San Quentin on an impossible mission to clear the name of Harrison Johnson (Hawthorne James), a death row inmate in Texas whom she believes has been wrongly accused of murders perpetrated by Ramirez (Lou Diamond Phillips). Kit lived in Los Angeles during the fear-tinged summer where Ramirez terrified its citizens and confronting him dredges up old and frightening memories of her own past. As the days count down to the Texas mans execution, Kit confronts Ramirez about his unspeakable crimes in search of an elusive confession, plunging into intense psychological depths in her quest for the truth.

programme.title: Happy Face Killer
programme.desc: Grisly serial killer Keith Hunter Jesperson taunts authorities with scribbled confessions bearing a smiley face at the scenes of his crimes. Based on a true story.

programme.title: Betrayed By Love
programme.desc: Carrie becomes distraught when a car accident takes her sister Rileys life. As the investigation commences, she discovers that the accident might not be the true cause of Rileys death.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Ruby
programme.desc: In the heart of the bayou, Ruby Landry lives a simple, happy life. The only family Ruby Landry has ever known are her loving guardian, Grandmere Catherine, a Cajun spiritual healer, and her drunken, outcast Grandpere Jack. Her life is filled with hope and promise, especially when her attraction for handsome Paul Tate blossoms into a mysterious, wonderful love. But Pauls wealthy parents forbid him to associate with a poor Landry while Grandmere urges her to follow her dream of becoming a great painter. In a faded photograph, Ruby glimpses for the first time the image of her father and learns of a shameful deception and a shocking scheme of blackmail that now must come to light. Stunned by these revelations, she is devastated when Grandmere dies, leaving her to seek out her father in his vast New Orleans mansion. There, in a house of lies, madness, and cruel torment, Ruby clings to her memories of Paul to keep her heart alive. For only their love can save her now.

programme.title: My Amish Double Life
programme.desc: Emma is a young Amish woman who leads a double life by sneaking out to clubs to flirt and have fun. However, when she accidentally witnesses a murder, her life and community get thrown into peril.

programme.title: Playing with Fire
programme.desc: After a near-fatal house fire, Natalie and Loughlin, a struggling married couple, are manipulated by an obsessive firefighter named Jack, who schemes to pit the couple against each other.

programme.title: Wrath: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Single lawyer Chastity Jeffries believes shes found her perfect match in Xavier Collins, but his obsessive love forces her to confront how far shes strayed from her own principles.

programme.title: Greed: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: When interior decorator Zuri Maxwell meets a handsome benefactor and entrepreneur, she compromises the values and morals that should guide her, in an effort to be part of his world.

programme.title: Blonde and Blonder
programme.desc: When two dim-witted blonde bombshells are mistaken for the underworlds most cunning assassins, they are approached with a lucrative contract to take out the head of the Chinese mafia in a globetrotting, air-headed comedy. Two fair-haired beauties have just witnessed a high-profile mob hit, and now the Godfather is convinced that they have what it takes to rub out his most fearsome rival. After accepting a hearty payout and agreeing to carry out the dangerous assignment, the two brainless beauties hit the open road on the adventure of a lifetime.

programme.title: A Model Murder
programme.desc: Model Kara Woods begins to get disturbing messages from one of her fans, causing her to seek help from a security influencer. Things are fine until Karas stalker shows up in person.

programme.title: Betrayed By Love
programme.desc: Carrie becomes distraught when a car accident takes her sister Rileys life. As the investigation commences, she discovers that the accident might not be the true cause of Rileys death.

programme.title: Britney Ever After
programme.desc: This is the tumultuous true story of Britney Jean Spears, one of the bestselling teenage music artists of all-time, whose dating life and public emotional breakdowns were the subjects of a worldwide media frenzy. By the age of 21, Britney Spears already had a number one platinum, debut album, a cover on Rolling Stone, a record-breaking second album, and international superstardom. Success in her personal life, however, would be much harder to achieve. A well-publicized romance and break-up with Justin Timberlake, a three-day marriage to a childhood sweetheart, and an ill-fated marriage to back-up dancer Kevin Federline made for a chaotic contrast to her record-setting music career.

programme.title: Who Killed JonBenet?
programme.desc: This Lifetime Original Movie revisits the infamous murder of pint-sized beauty queen JonBenet Ramsey and the lurid details that captivated the nation. Starting with the 911 call and investigation lead by Detective Steve Thomas, the film provides a closer look into what exactly happened the day after Christmas 1996, when she was found beaten and strangled in the familys basement. With the addition of recently surfaced information, the film takes a fresh look at the events and the competing theories about the murder. Were Patsy and John Ramsey responsible or covering for someone else in the family? Was this a kidnapping gone wrong, or was this the work of a predator who had seen JonBen t in one of her pageants? Twenty years after the tragic events, the question remains: Who killed JonBenet?

programme.title: Non-Stop
programme.desc: Having been jilted at the altar, a literary aide to a controversial author thinks nothing of a fleeting liaison with a man she meets on a business flight.

programme.title: Killer Fortune Teller
programme.desc: Shane Settel starts to believe in fate after a chance tarot reading. He has the largest success in his professional career and falls in love, but then tragedies begin to follow him.

programme.title: A Daughters Nightmare
programme.desc: After the death of her husband, Ariels mother Dana finds a friend in the mysterious Adam. When Danas health starts to fail, Ariel suspects Adam might not have the best of intentions.

programme.title: And Baby Will Fall
programme.desc: Expectant parents become prime suspects in the disappearance of a pregnant woman who was last seen at their garage sale.

programme.title: Expecting Amish
programme.desc: When an eventful Rumspringa leads to an unintended pregnancy, Amish teen Hannah must choose between returning to faith and family or beginning a new life elsewhere.

programme.title: Michael Jackson: Searching for Neverland
programme.desc: Based on Bill and Javons book Remember the Time: The Last Days of Michael Jackson, this movie will chronicle those intimate moments between Jackson and his children, document the professional turbulence that engulfed Jackson in financial trouble and forced him back to rehearsals for the ill-fated This Is It tour that led to his early death, and help answer the question that fans around the world want to know: What really happened to the King of Pop?

programme.title: Wife Stalker
programme.desc: Joannas obsessive fantasy of a perfect life with Leo shatters, forcing her to confront harsh reality and the truth about their relationship, with dire consequences.

programme.title: You Better Watch Out
programme.desc: Aubreys plane is grounded due to a snowstorm, leaving her stranded for the night at a small town airport. She stumbles into the middle of a kidnapping and throws herself into danger as she tries to save the young girl stranded with them.

programme.title: Husband, Father, Killer
programme.desc: Alyssa has a relationship with abusive Steven as a teen, has his child but gives it up for adoption. Years later, their daughter seeks them out, and Steven manipulates her into an affair, neglecting his family.

programme.title: My Sisters Serial Killer Boyfriend
programme.desc: Maddie, a local reporter investigating a series of killings targeting similar looking women is caught off guard when her younger sister Olivia, is attacked in her own home. Urging on the side of caution, Maddie suggests they take a self defence course. When Olivia starts to fall for their instructor, Maddie becomes sceptical when he refuses to reveal anything about himself, and tries to intervene before the relationship turns into a deadly obsession.

programme.title: Single Black Female
programme.desc: Monica is a young host of one of LAs top morning shows. Reeling from the death of her beloved father and the breakup she just suffered, shes ready to focus on moving forward with her life, and channelling all of her energy into getting the new hosting gig on the afternoon talk show at her station. She gets a new assistant, Simone, a beautiful biracial woman who is new in town and so excited to be supporting Monica. They become close quickly, with Simone moving in next door, and engraining herself into Monicas life. But underneath Simones sweet exterior lies a woman who harbors a dark secret, and is determined to become closer than close to Monica, whether she likes it or not! As time goes on, and Simone becomes more and more enmeshed in Monicas life, Monica starts to pick up on the cracks in Simones shiny facade. As she tries to pull back from Simone, Monica and those around her begin to fear that it may be too late - and even worse, that Simone may have had something to do with the death of her father and collapse of her relationship! Monica decides to sever ties with Simone once and for all, however, Simone has other plans. Will Monica get her life back, or will Simone succeed in taking over Monicas life for good?

programme.title: I Wont Let You Go
programme.desc: Inspired by true events. Angela West has always wanted a family, and now that she has one with her devoted husband Keith, she couldnt be happier. When an ex-boyfriend starts stalking her, Angela turns to Keith for protection. But no matter what she tries, she cant seem to shake the stalker who is ruining her life.

programme.title: I Was Octomom
programme.desc: In 2009, Natalie Suleman gives birth to eight children with the help of IVF, only to have her life torn apart, and her identity rebranded by the media.

programme.title: Lust: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Tiffanie is about to have the wedding of her dreams to her soul mate, the dashing Damon King, founder of King Enterprises. But when Damons old friend Trey arrives, fresh from prison to step in as Damons best man, Tiffanies whole world gets rocked. Sexy and mysterious, Trey triggers a passion in Tiffanie that she never expected, and suddenly the life shes always planned with Damon is uncertain. But Trey still carries wounds from his history with Damon, and his intentions toward both Tiffanie and Damon are not to be trusted.

programme.title: Envy: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Gabrielle Flores has it all - a devoted husband, a beautiful daughter, and one of the best PR firms in the country. When Gabrielles father suddenly reveals she has a half-sister, Keisha, as a result of a brief affair, only - child Gabrielle is delighted to welcome her into her life. But Keisha, who grew up with nothing, wants more than a sisterly bond from Gabrielle - she wants her life, and is willing to do whatever it takes to get it.

programme.title: Who Is Killing The Cheerleaders?
programme.desc: Ellie, a former cheerleader, returns to her high school as a teacher ten years after she was nearly killed in a series of brutal slayings on the squad. When the attacks start up again shortly after her arrival, she must find the killer before they get to her first.

programme.title: Framed by My Husband
programme.desc: When Junes wealthy husband Rick becomes the target of an extortionist who claims he sexually assaulted her, Rick convinces his wife its an act of revenge by a spurned suitor, and enlists her help to prevent the accusations from going public. June agrees to help him pay off the extortionist, but when the woman is found dead, June becomes the prime suspect.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Pearl In The Mist
programme.desc: Fate whisked Ruby from a simple life in the Louisiana Bayou. But her new riches bring more treachery than happiness. Even after a year as a Dumas, Ruby still wonders at the splendor of the familys New Orleans mansion and rejoices in the love of the father she had never known. But true happiness in her new home is as elusive as the swamp mist. Ruby must carefully avoid her venomous stepmother, Daphne, while making every effort to befriend her twin sister, Gisselle. While attending Greenwood, the exclusive girls boarding school, Ruby doesnt lose hope in a world that never really wanted her. Ruby will have to summon every last ounce of her Cajun strength to reclaim her home, her future, and the happiness she once knew.

programme.title: Beaches
programme.desc: While remaining faithful to the original story, we follow the lifelong friendship between LA-born CC Bloom and San Francisco rich girl Hillary Whitney after they serendipitously meet on Venice Beach. In this update, CC is a budding pop star who is struggling to make it in LA until she is discovered by a music producer who helps her develop her raw talent. Hillary is the daughter of a prominent lawyer who is intent on making her own destiny and getting out from under the control of her domineering father. Their friendship - even with its ups and downs - sustains them for decades, but ends tragically with Hillarys early death.

programme.title: Menendez: Blood Brothers
programme.desc: Erik and Lyle Menendez were educated, nice boys from sunny Beverly Hills, California. Erik was an exceptional tennis player and Lyle was studying at Princeton University. So when their parents were found shot dead in their home, no one could figure out why they would have done it? Everyone was perplexed. Was it for Money? For Fame? The case seemed closed, but that;s when the brothers revealed that they were sexually molested throughout their childhoods by their father, Jose. This was the trial that no one was ready for. Our story follows Erik and Lyle as they struggle with their overwhelming guilt, the harsh reality of abuse, incest and molestation that lead them down this path and the trial that shocked an entire nation of television watchers. Never before seen details emerge as we look closer into the lives of the Menendez brothers.

programme.title: A Roommate to Die For
programme.desc: After a nasty break-up, Faith needs a new roommate to supplement the rent and finds that something very strange is going on with the tenant who decides to move in.

programme.title: Love Triangle Nightmare
programme.desc: Brittany meets a stranger who has everything she wants in a partner and despite being an unknown man as warned by others, she falls in love with him which leads to something tragic.

programme.title: The Night Stalker
programme.desc: Known to many as the "Night Stalker", Richard Ramirez was a cruel and prolific serial killer who murdered 14 people and terrorized Los Angeles in the summer of 1985. This film tells the story of Kit (Bellamy Young), an attorney who travels to San Quentin on an impossible mission to clear the name of Harrison Johnson (Hawthorne James), a death row inmate in Texas whom she believes has been wrongly accused of murders perpetrated by Ramirez (Lou Diamond Phillips). Kit lived in Los Angeles during the fear-tinged summer where Ramirez terrified its citizens and confronting him dredges up old and frightening memories of her own past. As the days count down to the Texas mans execution, Kit confronts Ramirez about his unspeakable crimes in search of an elusive confession, plunging into intense psychological depths in her quest for the truth.

programme.title: Happy Face Killer
programme.desc: Grisly serial killer Keith Hunter Jesperson taunts authorities with scribbled confessions bearing a smiley face at the scenes of his crimes. Based on a true story.

programme.title: Betrayed By Love
programme.desc: Carrie becomes distraught when a car accident takes her sister Rileys life. As the investigation commences, she discovers that the accident might not be the true cause of Rileys death.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Ruby
programme.desc: In the heart of the bayou, Ruby Landry lives a simple, happy life. The only family Ruby Landry has ever known are her loving guardian, Grandmere Catherine, a Cajun spiritual healer, and her drunken, outcast Grandpere Jack. Her life is filled with hope and promise, especially when her attraction for handsome Paul Tate blossoms into a mysterious, wonderful love. But Pauls wealthy parents forbid him to associate with a poor Landry while Grandmere urges her to follow her dream of becoming a great painter. In a faded photograph, Ruby glimpses for the first time the image of her father and learns of a shameful deception and a shocking scheme of blackmail that now must come to light. Stunned by these revelations, she is devastated when Grandmere dies, leaving her to seek out her father in his vast New Orleans mansion. There, in a house of lies, madness, and cruel torment, Ruby clings to her memories of Paul to keep her heart alive. For only their love can save her now.

programme.title: Caddo Lake

programme.title: The Three Musketeers - Part II: Milady
programme.desc: Constance Bonacieux is kidnapped before DArtagnans very eyes. The young musketeer, aided by Athos, Porthos and Aramis, is forced to join the mysterious Milady de Winter.

programme.title: The Heist Before Christmas
programme.desc: A Christmas-hating boy meets two Santas in the woods, one of whom claims to have fallen from his sleigh, but he is more interested in the other man when he learns he is on the run for robbing a bank.

programme.title: Reagan

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: A young couple on their way home from a night of birthday celebrations is gunned down while getting gas. With the killers long since vanished, detectives must rely on the grainy gas station video.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Its July 30, 1995, a scorching San Diego summer day. An unidentified young woman is discovered by the side of the road, naked, raped, strangled to death, and thrown out like a piece of trash. Police have few clues but waste little time investigating this haunting crime. DNA matches the victim to 18-year-old Shannon Conway, a troubled teenage runaway who was living out of a sleeping bag among the hippies and transients on San Diegos Ocean Beach. An initial sweep zeroes in on several suspects. Tim Arman, Shannons ex-boyfriend, is still bitter that she dumped him a year ago. Keith Martin, a hobo living out of his van, is known as an angry Vietnam vet with a grudge against women. Martins van, eerily splattered with blood, was spotted in the area on the night of the murder. Police become convinced Martin is the killer but they cant forensically link him to the crime. Then a third suspect enters the frame. The day before Shannon was killed, she jumped into a pickup truck with a man she had met minutes before. Despite three strong leads, the San Diego Homicide struggle to put all the pieces together. Until over a decade later, new advances in DNA testing help cold case investigators finally find Shannons killer and give closure to her heart-broken mother.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Australia
programme.desc: On the 14 July 2001, British couple Peter Falconio and Joanne Lees stopped on the Stuart Highway in the Northern Territory after a man flagged down their car. This man, later identified as Bradley Murdoch, supposedly shot Falconio before tying Lees up and covering her head. She managed to escape while Murdoch was distracted, hiding in nearby bushes for five hours until she was able to run out into the road and flag down a truck driver who took her to safety. Falconios body has never been found. The subsequent trial and media furore would stun the nation as well as raising questions about the strength of the allegations against Murdoch.

programme.title: Crime Investigation Australia
programme.sub-title: Date With A Serial Killer - Rodney Cameron
programme.desc: Rodney Francis Cameron was dubbed The Lonely Hearts Killer after he used a radio matchmaking program in 1990 to lure an unsuspecting woman to her death. Incredibly, he had only just been released from prison for two other killings in 1974. Camerons psychopathic tendencies appeared early in his life. At the age of 10 he tried to strangle a young girl. He then attempted to strangle two other women and moved into a life of alcohol and drug abuse, including experimenting with hallucinogenic chemicals. He also dabbled in Satanism.

programme.title: #textmewhenyougethome

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: In Tucson, a young man is found shot to death on the street. Detectives Bill Hanson and Mike Carroll follow two clues that could lead to a suspect - a dropped cell phone and a pawnshop slip tucked in the victims pocket. In Memphis, Sergeant Debo Carson investigates the brutal murder of a woman whose body was found dumped on the railroad tracks. The case takes a dramatic turn when a tip comes in about a man who may know details about the murder that were never released to the media.

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: Nancy Dunning, Ronald Kirby, and Ruthanne Lodato were all fatally shot in broad daylight by a gunman knocking at the front door. Can detectives use security footage to track down a demented killer.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Lower Puna, Big Island, Hawaii, is a sun-kissed tropical playground drawing thousands of tourists. But in the shadows lurks another story of drugs, crime, and brutal violence. The two worlds collide on Christmas Eve, 1991, when 23-year-old tourist Dana Ireland takes a bike ride through paradise that ends in tragedy. Hit by a car, raped, and left for dead on a remote trail, Danas murder devastates her family and sends ripples of fear throughout the state. Police investigate a murky world few tourists ever see but come up empty. From the get-go, the police investigation is fraught. The crime scene evidence is messy, forensic technology cant connect the dots, and most suspects or witnesses are either tight-lipped or flat-out lying. When Danas father, furious with the polices lack of results, posts a $28,000 reward for any leads, lowlife tipsters come crawling out of the woodwork and overwhelm police with false information. Lead Detective, Steve Guillermo, is certain of only one fact - a small car struck Danas bike. The search for this vehicle takes over six years but upon finding it, Guillermo starts to untangle the web of lies. Three weeks before a statute of limitations ends on the prime suspects, Guillermo gets a break that closes the case for good.

programme.title: Booked: First Day In
programme.desc: Follows arrested individuals through Americas booking process, offering an extraordinary look at the most unusual, bizarre and often tense bookings. From petty offences to serious crimes, viewers will be taken on a harrowing adventure while they watch the arrestees throughout the booking process.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: In February 2000, eight-year-old Victoria Climbie died at St Marys Hospital, Middlesex. She had suffered the worst case of child abuse ever seen in the UK, at the hands of her aunt, Marie Therese Kouao, and an acquaintance, Carl Manning. Victoria had 128 separate injuries, which social services had failed to notice and act upon. As a result of her murder, the government conducted the biggest overhaul of the child protection service the UK had ever seen. The inquiry that followed took the unusual step of calling both Manning and Kouao to give evidence to try to understand how the authorities had failed Victoria so badly.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Lower Puna, Big Island, Hawaii, is a sun-kissed tropical playground drawing thousands of tourists. But in the shadows lurks another story of drugs, crime, and brutal violence. The two worlds collide on Christmas Eve, 1991, when 23-year-old tourist Dana Ireland takes a bike ride through paradise that ends in tragedy. Hit by a car, raped, and left for dead on a remote trail, Danas murder devastates her family and sends ripples of fear throughout the state. Police investigate a murky world few tourists ever see but come up empty. From the get-go, the police investigation is fraught. The crime scene evidence is messy, forensic technology cant connect the dots, and most suspects or witnesses are either tight-lipped or flat-out lying. When Danas father, furious with the polices lack of results, posts a $28,000 reward for any leads, lowlife tipsters come crawling out of the woodwork and overwhelm police with false information. Lead Detective, Steve Guillermo, is certain of only one fact - a small car struck Danas bike. The search for this vehicle takes over six years but upon finding it, Guillermo starts to untangle the web of lies. Three weeks before a statute of limitations ends on the prime suspects, Guillermo gets a break that closes the case for good.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: Among the first US Navy vessels to see action in the Pacific in WWII were the motor torpedo boats of PT Boat Squadron 3 in the Philippines during the Japanese invasion. And for the next three years, from Guadalcanal to the coasts of Japan, they ran reconnaissance and screening missions, landed raiding parties, and attacked enemy shore installations and supply barges. See how they lived up to the motto of John Paul Jones: "Give me a fast ship, for I intend to go in harms way."

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: In the aerial battleground of World War II, the P-51 Mustang proved itself to be the most famous war bird in history. Take a look at three of its most memorable battles. On November 2, 1944, Capt Donald Bryan leads a group of P-51s escorting B-24 bombers to their target deep inside of Germany when he runs into a huge gaggle of Me109s on the attack. On June 23, 1945, 2d Lt Bob Scamara takes off with a flight of Mustangs from Iwo Jima. His group is jumped by 17 Zeroes. On April 7, 1945, pilot Richard Candelaria becomes one of the first Americans to face the jet menace.

programme.title: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Today it is easy to see D-Day as an inevitable - a straightforward victory against a German army that was already all but defeated. This film explodes that myth. It charts the careful planning of the campaign, the development of specialised equipment needed for the amphibious landing. It reveals the deception plan that wrong-footed Hitler. It shows how the Americans were very nearly driven off Omaha beach. If that had happened, the whole operation might have failed. The film ends with the liberation of Paris, as the Free French forces led by Charles de Gaulle marched down the streets of the capital. Conventional wisdom has recently changed as more and more secrets have been revealed, particularly in the last five to 10 years as documents, files and photographs have been released. Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters
programme.desc: The hunt for Albert Speer, someone whose crimes included using and organising slave labour in death camps and prolonging the war with his fanatical work to develop the Nazi war machine.

programme.desc: A field near the east coast of the Isle of Wight. Scatterings of early pottery, some fine Roman metalwork, but as yet no signs of any buildings. The area is known for at least one grand Roman villa; could this be the site of a second?

programme.title: Walking Through History
programme.sub-title: Englands Last Battle: The West Country
programme.desc: Appealing to history buffs and dedicated ramblers alike, Sir Tony Robinson embarks on spectacular walks through some of Britains most historic landscapes in search of the richest stories from Britains past. In each programme, Tony follows a bespoke route that allows him to explore on foot both the history of a particularly colourful historical period or event, and the spectacular landscape in which those events unfolded. The walks are proper expeditions with each one taking Tony several days. With various experts he encounters on the way, Tony reveals and discovers places and their hidden stories that ordinary walkers and ramblers might otherwise miss. And, as well as the history, Tony infuses each walk with an appreciation of some of the striking landscapes and geographical features Britain contains.

programme.desc: Today it is easy to see D-Day as an inevitable - a straightforward victory against a German army that was already all but defeated. This film explodes that myth. It charts the careful planning of the campaign, the development of specialised equipment needed for the amphibious landing. It reveals the deception plan that wrong-footed Hitler. It shows how the Americans were very nearly driven off Omaha beach. If that had happened, the whole operation might have failed. The film ends with the liberation of Paris, as the Free French forces led by Charles de Gaulle marched down the streets of the capital. Conventional wisdom has recently changed as more and more secrets have been revealed, particularly in the last five to 10 years as documents, files and photographs have been released. Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Walking Through History
programme.sub-title: Englands Last Battle: The West Country
programme.desc: Appealing to history buffs and dedicated ramblers alike, Sir Tony Robinson embarks on spectacular walks through some of Britains most historic landscapes in search of the richest stories from Britains past. In each programme, Tony follows a bespoke route that allows him to explore on foot both the history of a particularly colourful historical period or event, and the spectacular landscape in which those events unfolded. The walks are proper expeditions with each one taking Tony several days. With various experts he encounters on the way, Tony reveals and discovers places and their hidden stories that ordinary walkers and ramblers might otherwise miss. And, as well as the history, Tony infuses each walk with an appreciation of some of the striking landscapes and geographical features Britain contains.

programme.desc: Gary wakes from his coma, and thanks Ray for doing "a bit of this and a bit of that" to Vassili and the guys who bashed him. Gary, who has just returned home from hospital, manages to send an SOS text to Ray who is out shopping with Ally. Ray comes to Garys rescue and promptly deals with Vasilli - but theyll have to work out what to do with the body as Tatiana has arrived home unexpectedly.

programme.title: Mr Inbetween
programme.desc: Gary takes Ray for a drive to give him a surprise as a thank you for saving him. Ray and Allys relationship has developed. Freddy takes Ray to meet Davros. For Ray, its all about respect. Ray brings Ally home to meet Brittany. Ray cant sleep and gets up to notice a van parked outside surveilling his house. He goes for a drive and leads the van out to a safe place to do some permanent damage to its occupants - Davros guys - using the surprise Gary gave him.
